Head broader than body, narrowing at the posterior. Pronotum narrow, widening towards posterior, twice as long as wide. Mesonotum widening evenly from about 4.0 mm at anterior to 5.0 mm at posterior, rest of body of uniform almost width (5.0– 
5.5 mm
). Metanotum and median segment of equal length. Body without any lobes or spines. Abdominal segments I–VI of increasing length, VII equal to II, combined length of VIII– IX less than VII. Segments X–IX with slight longitudinal carina. Supraanal plate short, triangular (Fig. 257). Apex of sternum VII with a depression. Abdominal tergites VII–XI, sternum VII, and subgenital plate sethose. Subgenital plate straight with a fine longitudinal carina, apex rounded (Figs 258–259), 1.0 mm longer than abdomen in HT, 3.0 mm in PT. Cerci conical, apex slightly upturned. Gonapophyses protruding slightly beyond supraanal plate.
